      "weather": "Fine",
      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "THAT'S MY BOY (8) is in hot form after clocking a handy 25.95 victory two back then followed up with a 26.50 win at this track over 460m last time. Hard to top on recent times. BULL DURHAM (1) settled down midfield and held his position to the line when finishing 4th (23.03) at Geelong. Solid record here at the distance winning five races. Goes well out of this box with a win and four minor placings. Worth another chance. FURY'S RAGE (2) had some strong recent form but was below best last time when sixth (22.55) in a Grade 4/5 at Shepparton. Normally safe to begin but shuffled back last time off the low draw. The form out of the last run is proven to be strong. Can measure up this time. I'M HONEY (7) is a last start winner who can measure up again.",
